<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head> Kidney Precision Medicine Project</head></div>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head>Background</head><p>Glomerular histomorphology establishes kidney disease diagnosis and prognosis. Spatial transcriptomics facilitates spatial resolution of molecular signatures superimposed upon histology. We trained a machine learning (ML) method to automatically segment glomeruli and quantify pixel level image features to align with spatial transcriptomics (ST) performed on the same section.</p></div>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head>Methods</head></div>
			</abstract>
